First Lady Melania Trump visited Children's National Hospital in Washington, D.C., where she toured the neuroscience center, read a holiday book to patients, and answered questions about the holidays. She expressed gratitude for the opportunity to spend time with the children and their families and thanked the medical staff for their work. Melania Trump emphasized that the holidays are a time for hope, love, traditions, and family, and she wished for everyone to be able to celebrate in good health with their loved ones. She asked people to keep the patients and families she visited in their thoughts and prayers for a speedy recovery and a joyous New Year.